      "message": "[error] Line 974: Logic is asymmetric: only the `true→false` transition triggers a reconnect. When `dhtPublicInCalls` is currently `false` and the new value is `true`, the early `return false` fires and existing connections are never reset to adopt the new public-DHT setting. Fix: compare the current and incoming values regardless of direction, e.g. `auto it \u003d details.find(...); if (it \u003d\u003d details.end()) return false; return (it-\u003esecond \u003d\u003d TRUE_STR) !\u003d config().dhtPublicInCalls;`",
